`.lit` is the culmination of a few not so disperate ideas: [[Literate Programming]], [[Interactive Notebooks]], [[Digital Gardens]] and [[Wiki]].

Meant to enable [[Guided Learning]] ‚Äî where the author shows the reader by *tactile* example; and exploration or [[Rapid Prototyping]] while trying not to be a separate system from which a student or project *graduates* but which is itself *[[an acceptable development evironment]]*.
